      "comment": "RUBICK DELIGHT (9) improved nicely second-up to get the job done in a Maiden last time out when sitting on the speed at Geraldton. The good draw should see her prominent in the run and she can improve again third-up into the campaign. Can go on with the job. THE RUSH (1) finished eighth over 1600m at Geraldton last time out following a determined win two back. Will find this a little easier than last time. Well placed and is one of the contenders. RUN TEDDY RUN (10) was never really a threat when resuming last start over 1400m at Belmont Park, finishing 7 lengths from the winner in eighth. Has a win and three minor placings at this journey from six starts and is not to be discounted. LIM'S SARBACH (3) is next.",
